==Events== * [[814]] &ndash; [[Charlemagne]] dies of [[pleurisy]] in [[Aachen]] as the first [[Holy Roman Emperor]]. He is succeeded by his son [[Louis the Pious]] as king of the [[Carolingian Empire|Frankish Empire]]. * [[946]] &ndash; Caliph [[Al-Mustakfi]] is blinded and deposed by Emir [[Mu'izz al-Dawla]], ruler of the [[Buyid dynasty|Buyid Empire]]. He is succeeded by [[Al-Muti]] as caliph of the [[Abbasid Caliphate]]. *[[1069]] &ndash; [[Robert de Comines]], the [[Earl of Northumbria]], is killed while attempting to subdue rebels in [[Durham, England]]. This leads to the [[Harrying of the North]] by [[William the Conqueror]]. *[[1077]] &ndash; [[Walk to Canossa]]: The [[excommunication]] of [[Henry IV, Holy Roman Emperor]] is lifted. *[[1393]] &ndash; King [[Charles VI of France]] is nearly killed when [[Bal des Ardents|several dancers' costumes catch fire]] during a [[masquerade ball]]. *[[1521]] &ndash; The [[Diet of Worms]] begins, lasting until [[May 25]]. *[[1547]] &ndash; [[Henry VIII of England|Henry VIII]] dies. His nine-year-old son, [[Edward VI of England|Edward VI]], becomes king. *[[1568]] &ndash; The [[Edict of Torda]] prohibited the persecution of individuals on religious ground in [[John Sigismund Zápolya]]'s [[Eastern Hungarian Kingdom]]. *[[1573]] &ndash; Articles of the [[Warsaw Confederation]] are signed, sanctioning [[freedom of religion]] in Poland. *[[1624]] &ndash; [[Thomas Warner (explorer)|Sir Thomas Warner]] founds the first British colony in the Caribbean, on the island of [[Saint Kitts]]. *[[1724]] &ndash; The [[Russian Academy of Sciences]] is founded in [[St. Petersburg]] by [[Peter the Great]], and implemented by Senate decree. It is called the St. Petersburg Academy of Sciences until 1917. *[[1754]] &ndash; Sir [[Horace Walpole]] coins the word ''[[serendipity]]'' in a letter to a friend. *[[1813]] &ndash; [[Jane Austen]]'s ''[[Pride and Prejudice]]'' is first published in the [[United Kingdom]]. *[[1846]] &ndash; The [[Battle of Aliwal]], [[India]], is won by British troops commanded by [[Sir Harry Smith, 1st Baronet|Sir Harry Smith]]. *[[1851]] &ndash; [[Northwestern University]] becomes the first chartered university in [[Illinois]]. *[[1855]] &ndash; A locomotive on the [[Panama Canal Railway]] runs from the Atlantic Ocean to the Pacific Ocean for the first time. *[[1871]] &ndash; [[Franco-Prussian War]]: The [[Siege of Paris (1870–71)|Siege of Paris]] ends in French defeat and an armistice. *[[1878]] &ndash; ''[[Yale Daily News]]'' becomes the first daily [[Student newspaper|college newspaper]] in the [[United States]]. *[[1896]] &ndash; Walter Arnold of [[East Peckham]], Kent, becomes the first person to be convicted of [[speed limit|speeding]]. He was fined one [[shilling (British coin)|shilling]], plus costs, for speeding at {{convert|8|mph|km/h|abbr=on}}, thereby exceeding the contemporary speed limit of {{convert|2|mph|km/h|abbr=on}}. *[[1902]] &ndash; The [[Carnegie Institution for Science|Carnegie Institution of Washington]] is founded in Washington, D.C. with a $10 million gift from [[Andrew Carnegie]]. *[[1908]] &ndash; Members of the [[Portuguese Republican Party]] fail in their [[Municipal Library Elevator Coup|attempted coup d'état]] against the administrative dictatorship of Prime Minister [[João Franco]]. *[[1909]] &ndash; United States troops leave [[Cuba]] with the exception of [[Guantanamo Bay Naval Base]] after being there since the [[Spanish–American War]]. *[[1915]] &ndash; An act of the [[United States Congress|U.S. Congress]] creates the [[United States Coast Guard]] as a branch of the United States Armed Forces. *[[1918]] &ndash; [[Finnish Civil War]]: The [[Red Guards (Finland)|Red Guard rebels]] seize control of the capital, [[Helsinki]]; members of the [[Senate of Finland]] go underground. *[[1920]] &ndash; Foundation of the [[Spanish Legion]]. *[[1922]] &ndash; [[Knickerbocker Storm]], Washington D.C.'s biggest snowfall, causes the city's greatest loss of life when the roof of the [[Knickerbocker Theatre (Washington, D.C.)|Knickerbocker Theatre]] collapses. *[[1932]] &ndash; Japanese forces [[January 28 Incident|attack Shanghai]]. *[[1933]] &ndash; The name [[Pakistan]] is [[Neologism|coined]] by [[Choudhry Rahmat Ali|Choudhry Rahmat Ali Khan]] and is accepted by [[Indian Muslims]] who then thereby adopted it further for the [[Pakistan Movement]] seeking independence. *[[1935]] &ndash; [[Iceland]] becomes the first Western country to legalize therapeutic [[abortion]]. *[[1938]] &ndash; The [[World Land Speed Record]] on a [[public road]] is broken by [[Rudolf Caracciola]] in the [[Mercedes-Benz W195]] at a speed of {{convert|432.7|km/h|mph}}. *[[1941]] &ndash; [[Franco-Thai War]]: Final air battle of the conflict. A Japanese-mediated [[armistice]] goes into effect later in the day. *[[1945]] &ndash; [[World War II]]: Supplies begin to reach the [[Republic of China (1912–49)|Republic of China]] over the newly reopened [[Burma Road]]. *[[1956]] &ndash; [[Elvis Presley]] makes his first national television appearance. *[[1958]] &ndash; The [[Lego]] company patents the design of its Lego bricks, still compatible with bricks produced today. *[[1960]] &ndash; The [[National Football League]] announced expansion teams for [[Dallas Cowboys|Dallas]] to start in the 1960 NFL season and [[Minnesota Vikings|Minneapolis-St. Paul]] for 1961 NFL season. *[[1964]] &ndash; An unarmed [[United States Air Force]] [[T-39 Sabreliner]] on a training mission is [[1964 T-39 shootdown incident|shot down]] over [[Erfurt]], [[East Germany]], by a [[Soviet Air Forces|Soviet]] [[MiG-19]]. *[[1965]] &ndash; The current design of the [[Flag of Canada]] is chosen by an act of [[Parliament of Canada|Parliament]]. *[[1977]] &ndash; The first day of the [[Great Lakes Blizzard of 1977]] which dumps {{convert|10|ft|m}} of snow in one day in [[Upstate New York]], with [[Buffalo, New York|Buffalo]], [[Syracuse, New York|Syracuse]], [[Watertown, New York|Watertown]], and surrounding areas are most affected. *[[1980]] &ndash; {{USCGC|Blackthorn|WLB-391|6}} collides with the tanker Capricorn while leaving [[Tampa, Florida]] and capsizes, killing 23 Coast Guard crewmembers. *[[1981]] &ndash; [[Ronald Reagan]] lifts remaining domestic petroleum price and allocation controls in the United States helping to end the [[1979 energy crisis]] and begin the [[1980s oil glut]]. *[[1982]] &ndash; [[United States Army|US Army]] general [[James L. Dozier]] is rescued by Italian anti-[[terrorism]] forces from captivity by the [[Red Brigades]]. *[[1984]] &ndash; [[Tropical Storm Domoina]] makes landfall in southern [[Mozambique]], eventually causing 214 deaths and some of the most severe flooding so far recorded in the region. *[[1985]] &ndash; Supergroup [[USA for Africa]] (United Support of Artists for Africa) records the hit single ''[[We Are the World]]'', to help raise funds for [[Ethiopia]]n [[famine relief]]. *[[1986]] &ndash; [[Space Shuttle program]]: [[STS-51-L]] mission: [[Space Shuttle Challenger]] [[Space Shuttle Challenger disaster|disintegrates after liftoff]], killing all seven astronauts on board. *[[1988]] &ndash; In ''[[R v Morgentaler]]'' the Supreme Court of Canada strikes down all anti-[[abortion law]]s. *[[2002]] &ndash; [[TAME Flight 120]], a [[Boeing 727]]-100 crashes in the [[Andes]] mountains in southern [[Colombia]], killing 92. *[[2006]] &ndash; The roof of one of the buildings at the [[Katowice International Fair]] in Poland, [[Katowice Trade Hall roof collapse|collapses]] due to the weight of snow, killing 65 and injuring more than 170 others. *[[2016]] - The [[World Health Organization]] announces an outbreak of the [[Zika virus]].
